                <h2>My Stories</h2>
                <ul>
                  <li>Endless Blue: In a world where magic exists but has been outlawed by the church on penalty of death, Minerva Ignatius, the daughter of a blacksmith lives a peaceful and uneventful life. However, with the sudden destruction of her hometown by mercenaries, something she believes is her fault, she must strike out on a journey of atonement. Along the way she meets allies like the white-haired church priestess Sara, and witty mage-thief Lena, all while hiding the fact that she can use magic. This series spans four books and is currently in the editing stage.</li>
                  <li>Crystaria (name pending): Laurel lives in the forest, one with nature and without shoes, alongside her father, a woodcutter, her mother having left when she was little for reasons unknown. When mysterious men in a strange flying vessel destroy her village, she is forced to flee the forest. Along the way she finds allies such as a large metal man she nicknames "Steam Man" and Liza, a mysterious scholar of the magical arts. Soon, she finds herself in the middle of a brutal conflict between nations and facing a conspiracy that could tear Crystaria asunder.</li>
                  <li>Star-Crossed: Strait-laced university honor student Emily Ashton could care less about happenings beyond the stars, but when an alien crash-lands into her life and changes her life forever, her entire world is turned unpside-down. This slice-of-life story follows the story of Emily and the alien girl Astraea and their day-to-day interactions of Emily showing Astraea what it means to live life on Earth.</li>
                </ul>

